# setTimeout Function

The setTimeout function allows you to delay your functions from executing.

Syntax:
```
setTimeout(function, time)
```
Examples:
```
let myPromise =  new  Promise(function(myResolve, myReject){

setTimeout(function(){ myResolve("I love you !!");}, 3000)

});

  

myPromise.then(function(value){

console.log(value);

});
This logs "I love you" to the console after 3 seconds
```
